    <div id="source-tab" class="content-tab-panel">
<table><tr><td>Centre of Perinatal Excellence (COPE). Mental health care in the perinatal period: Australian clinical practice guideline. Melbourne (Australia): Centre of Perinatal Excellence (COPE); 2017 Oct. 120 p.  [196 references]</td></tr></table>                    <p><a href="/web/20180712165112/https://www.guideline.gov/Home/Disclaimer?id=51300&amp;contentType=fulltextlink&amp;redirect=http%253a%252f%252fcope.org.au%252fwp-content%252fuploads%252f2017%252f10%252fFinal-COPE-Perinatal-Mental-Health-Guideline.pdf">View the original guideline documentation</a>&nbsp;<img alt="External Web Site Policy" src="/web/20180712165112im_/https://www.guideline.gov/UI/images/icon_externallink.gif"/></p>
    </div>
    <!-- /.content-tab-panel -->
    <div id="status-tab" class="content-tab-panel">
            <p><div class="content_para"><p>This is the current release of the guideline.</p>
<p>This guideline updates a previous version: Austin M-P, Highet N, Guidelines Expert Advisory Committee. Australian clinical practice guidelines for depression and related disorders -- anxiety, bipolar disorder and puerperal psychosis -- in the perinatal period. A guideline for primary health care professionals. Melbourne (Australia): beyondblue: the national depression initiative; 2011 Feb. 108 p. [293 references]</p>
<p>This guideline meets NGC's 2013 (revised) inclusion criteria.</p></div></p>
    </div>
    <!-- /.content-tab-panel -->
